# ─── Personal data (stays local after onboarding) ───
# setup.sh auto-disconnects from the template remote,
# so your data never gets pushed to the public repo.
# If you use your own private remote, all files are safe to track.
.loci/status.yml
.loci/activity-log.md
# .loci/config.yml is intentionally tracked (not gitignored).
# It contains persistence/routing/privacy settings that should be version-controlled
# so your brain configuration is portable and restorable. No secrets are stored here.
